                  </persName>
             (Police-constable N 143.) I stopped the prisoner, and found on him two pieces of beef - they were produced before the Magistrate, and sworn to; the prisoner said he had bought them both.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183209060177"></xptr>JOHN HARRADENCE. The prisoner took two pieces of beef, but only paid for one, with one half-crown; he then went over the way, and tied up the two pieces in a handkerchief - he then went and had some oysters: I followed him till I saw the officer.</p>
               <p>
